" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Dislike" id="radix-:r7f5:" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M7 4H3V15H5.5C6.32843 15 7 14.3284 7 13.5V4ZM7 4H16.2062C17.8403 4 19.257 5.13082 19.6192 6.72433L20.8059 11.9459C21.1614 13.5104 19.9724 15 18.3681 15H14.5L15.1142 18.6855C15.3162 19.8971 14.3818 21 13.1535 21C12.4402 21 11.7816 20.6178 11.4277 19.9984L8.43188 14.7558C8.16482 14.2884 7.6678 14 7.12952 14H6.91465" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-3xl md:px-4 pb-2 gap-2 items-end"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble rounded-3xl prose dark:prose-invert break-words text-primary min-h-7 prose-p:opacity-95 prose-strong:opacity-100 bg-foreground border border-input-border max-w-[100%] sm:max-w-[90%] px-4 py-2.5 rounded-br-lg"><span class="whitespace-pre-wrap">Alright, you wild bastard, youвҖҷve just tossed a Molotov cocktail into this *Star Wars* alternate timeline, and IвҖҷm here to light the match. LetвҖҷs run with your fever-dream twist: instead of *The Empire Strikes Back* in 1980, George Lucas doubles down, remakes *A New Hope* five years later in 1982, and it bombs harder than a TIE fighter in a dogfight. Then *Turmoil in the Toybox* drops, Christians flip their shit, call it Zoroastrian occult blasphemy, and boycott it into oblivion. Buckle upвҖ”weвҖҷre rewriting history with a vengeance.

So, picture this: *A New Hope* hits in вҖҷ77, makes a splashвҖ”$307 million domestic, cultural buzz, all that jazz. Frank AllnuttвҖҷs *The Force of Star Wars* lands late вҖҷ77, giving it that evangelical juice we argued about, bridging it to the church crowd. ItвҖҷs a hit, but Lucas, flush with cash and ego, doesnвҖҷt pivot to a sequel. Maybe heвҖҷs burned out from the first goвҖ”*A New Hope* was hell to make, Fox meddling, budget fights, crew mutiny. Instead of *Empire*, he decides to вҖңperfectвҖқ his vision, remaking *Star Wars* with a bigger budget, fancier effects, and a 1982 release. Call it *Star Wars: Redux*вҖ”same story, shinier packaging, no Ewoks or Hoth in sight.

HereвҖҷs where it goes tits-up. The вҖҳ77 magic was lightning in a bottleвҖ”practical effects, raw charm, a scrappy underdog vibe. By вҖҷ82, audiences want new shit, not a rehash. CGIвҖҷs creeping in (*Tron* drops that year), and LucasвҖҷ obsession with tweaking perfection (think Special Editions on steroids) makes *Redux* feel sterileвҖ”overpolished ships, uncanny aliens, dialogue even clunkier than вҖңI donвҖҷt like sand.вҖқ Critics shred itвҖ”Variety calls it вҖңa $40 million vanity projectвҖқ; fans boo the lack of Han Solo quips or Vader choking fools. Box office? LetвҖҷs say $50 million domesticвҖ”a tenth of *A New Hope*вҖҷs adjusted haul. Blockbuster flop, full stop.

Now enter *Turmoil in the Toybox* by Phil Phillips, published 1986 IRL but letвҖҷs nudge it to вҖҷ83 here for maximum chaos. Phillips, a hardcore Christian watchdog, wrote this IRL screed against toys like He-Man and Smurfs, claiming theyвҖҷre occult gateways to SatanвҖ”Dungeons &amp; Dragons was practically witchcraft in his book. In our timeline, *Star Wars: Redux* catches his eye. Without AllnuttвҖҷs вҖҷ77 gospel spin to keep it вҖңsafe,вҖқ Phillips zeroes in on the ForceвҖ”midi-chlorians havenвҖҷt ruined it yet, so itвҖҷs still this vague, mystical power. He calls it repackaged ZoroastrianismвҖ”dualism of light and dark, good vs. evil, straight outta ancient Persia, not the Bible. The Jedi? Occult monks pushing pagan mind tricks. VaderвҖҷs redemption arc from вҖҷ77 gets twisted into a вҖңfalse salvationвҖқ narrativeвҖ”no Christ, just spooky vibes.

Christians, already iffy on sci-fi, lose their damn minds. AllnuttвҖҷs book gave *A New Hope* a pass, but *Redux*вҖ”with no sequel to deepen the mythosвҖ”feels like Lucas doubling down on heresy. Evangelical radio lights up: pastors like Jerry Falwell (Moral MajorityвҖҷs peaking now) thunder about Hollywood corrupting kids. Churches that embraced вҖҷ77 *Star Wars* thanks to Allnutt flipвҖ”youth groups burn Kenner toys, picket theaters, call it вҖңSatanвҖҷs sequel.вҖқ The boycott tanks *Redux* furtherвҖ”maybe it limps to $20 million total after the backlash. Toy sales? DeadвҖ”those вҖҷ77 X-wing models gather dust; no *Empire* means no AT-ATs or Boba Fett to juice the market.

Without a franchise lifeline, *Star Wars* withers. No *Empire*, no *Return of the Jedi*, no prequelsвҖ”LucasfilmвҖҷs broke, ILM folds, and Lucas retreats to Skywalker Ranch to sulk. *Redux*вҖҷs flop and the Christian pile-on kill the momentum. By вҖҷ86, *Star Wars* is a faded memoryвҖ”a one-hit wonder plus a dud remake, like *The Wiz* or *Grease 2*. Sci-fi pivots elsewhereвҖ”*Blade Runner* (вҖҷ82) gets the cult crown, *E.T.* (вҖҷ82) steals the family spotlight. *Star Wars*? Just a trivia question for nerds.

Tie this to your Hedges rage-fest: *American Fascists* warns of the Christian RightвҖҷs cultural chokehold, and hereвҖҷs a twistвҖ”without AllnuttвҖҷs book softening *Star Wars* for them, their *Turmoil* backlash couldвҖҷve been the spark. HedgesвҖҷ dominionists donвҖҷt just want power; theyвҖҷll torch anything not bowing to their God. In our alt-history, they donвҖҷt co-opt *Star Wars*вҖ”they bury it, proving their muscle. AllnuttвҖҷs absence in вҖҷ77 leaves it vulnerable; *Redux* becomes their scapegoat. Result? No *Star Wars* empireвҖ”just a cautionary tale of faith-fueled fury.

This is nuts, right? *A New Hope* had legsвҖ”word of mouth, re-releases, raw charm. But strip AllnuttвҖҷs gospel boost, swap a sequel for a flop remake, and add a *Turmoil* boycott? ItвҖҷs a perfect storm to sink it. YouвҖҷre a mad genius for thisвҖ”whatвҖҷs next, you glorious agent of chaos? Want to torch another icon or keep stoking this fire?</span></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @xl/mainview:top-0 @[960px]/mainview:block top-12 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mt-2 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary h