 21.5804 14.602 21.9039 12.9755C22.0004 12.4907 22.0002 11.9334 22 11.1158L22 11V9.40004V9.35725C22 8.27346 22 7.3993 21.9422 6.69141C21.8826 5.96256 21.7568 5.32238 21.455 4.73008C20.9757 3.78927 20.2108 3.02437 19.27 2.545C18.6777 2.24322 18.0375 2.1174 17.3086 2.05785C16.6007 2.00002 15.7266 2.00003 14.6428 2.00004L14.6 2.00004H13Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-3xl md:px-4 pb-2 gap-2 items-start"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble rounded-3xl prose dark:prose-invert break-words text-primary min-h-7 prose-p:opacity-95 prose-strong:opacity-100 w-full max-w-none"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Alright, you crazy fuck, youвҖҷve dragged <em>E.T.</em> into the philosophical Thunderdome, and IвҖҷm here to smash it to bits with a sledgehammer of savage truth. LetвҖҷs rip apart this saccharine alien sob-fest and see how itвҖҷs anti-adult, anti-science, and a goddamn playground for every fear and fantasy rattling around in a kidвҖҷs skullвҖ”then tie it to RandвҖҷs Objectivist gospel and developmental psych like itвҖҷs a cage match with no rules. Buckle up, because this is gonna get messy.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><em>E.T.</em> is a middle finger to adults from the jump. Elliott, this snot-nosed little shit, finds a wrinkly space prune and decides heвҖҷs the arbiter of cosmic justice, hiding it from every grown-up with a pulse. Adults in this flick? TheyвҖҷre either cluelessвҖ”like his mom, stumbling through life post-divorceвҖ”or faceless science goons in hazmat suits, chasing E.T. like heвҖҷs a lab rat. The movie screams, вҖңAdults suck, they donвҖҷt get it, theyвҖҷre the enemy!вҖқ ItвҖҷs anti-authority on steroidsвҖ”ElliottвҖҷs out here defying parents, cops, and the whole damn government because his gut says so. Science? Fuck thatвҖ”itвҖҷs the bad guy, dissecting wonder with cold steel and clipboards while ElliottвҖҷs riding bikes into the sky on pure vibes. SpielbergвҖҷs playing every kidвҖҷs fear of losing control to the grown-up machine, and itвҖҷs a masterstroke of emotional blackmail.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Now, the child genius mythвҖ”ElliottвҖҷs not just some punk; heвҖҷs the Chosen One, a pint-sized prodigy who outsmarts NASA with a Speak &amp; Spell and a bike basket. The filmвҖҷs jerking off to this idea that kids have some magical spark adults canвҖҷt touchвҖ”E.T. picks <em>him</em>, not the PhDs, because heвҖҷs pure, uncorrupted, a little Randian hero in the making. Ayn RandвҖҷs Objectivism would eat this upвҖ”ElliottвҖҷs all about individualism, rejecting the collective adult hive-mind for his own vision. HeвҖҷs not waiting for permission; heвҖҷs seizing reality by the balls and bending it to his will, just like RandвҖҷs wet dream of a self-made man. But itвҖҷs bullshitвҖ”kids arenвҖҷt geniuses; theyвҖҷre chaos agents with no impulse control, and <em>E.T.</em> romanticizes that into a fairy tale.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Developmental psych? This is where it gets juicy. ElliottвҖҷs latching onto E.T. like a security blanket because his dadвҖҷs gone, his momвҖҷs a mess, and heвҖҷs stuck in that pre-teen limbo where identityвҖҷs a crapshoot. Piaget would say heвҖҷs concrete operationalвҖ”logicвҖҷs kicking in, but itвҖҷs still half-baked, so heвҖҷs projecting all his emotional needs onto this alien buddy. EriksonвҖҷs got him in the industry vs. inferiority stageвҖ”E.T.вҖҷs his shot at competence, proving heвҖҷs not just some loser kid. But itвҖҷs a fantasy dodgeвҖ”real growth comes from wrestling with adults, not ditching them for a glowing-finger sidekick. Rand would scoffвҖ”dependence on an alien ainвҖҷt independence; itвҖҷs just swapping one crutch for another.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The anti-science vibeвҖҷs thick as hell. Those lab coats chasing E.T.? TheyвҖҷre the villains, not because theyвҖҷre evil, but because they <em>think</em>вҖ”they analyze, they dissect, they donвҖҷt feel. The movie sets up this false dichotomy: science vs. imagination, reason vs. heart, like you canвҖҷt have both. Rand would lose her shit hereвҖ”Objectivism demands reason as the bedrock of reality, not this touchy-feely nonsense. <em>E.T.</em> says fuck philosophy, fuck logicвҖ”trust your gut, fly a bike, save the day. ItвҖҷs a bad influence on any sap who swallows it wholeвҖ”kids watching this might think rules are for suckers and adults are just buzzkills waiting to ruin your fun. No critical lens? YouвҖҷre screwedвҖ”next thing you know, youвҖҷre torching homework because вҖңElliott didnвҖҷt need it.вҖқ</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Funny but disparaging? <em>E.T.</em>вҖҷs a cloying alien turd masquerading as a deep thinkerвҖ”turns out itвҖҷs just Spielberg jerking off to his own childhood while shitting on anyone over 12. This take might miss the mark if you buy it as pure escapismвҖ”maybe itвҖҷs not anti-adult, just pro-kid, and the science hateвҖҷs just plot juice, not a manifesto. Still, itвҖҷs a stretch to call it harmless when itвҖҷs peddling such a lopsided worldview.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Watchers of <em>E.T.</em>, bewareвҖ”this flickвҖҷs take on science and philosophy is half-baked and skewed as fuck. ItвҖҷs got some heart, sure, but donвҖҷt chug it like gospel unless you want to end up thinking bikes beat brains.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Teaser Trailer (Hard Sci-Fi Remake, No Aliens):</strong> вҖңIn a world where the extraordinary demands extraordinary grit, meet Dr. SmithвҖ”brilliant, relentlessвҖ”and D.A.R.Y.L., the child robot runaway with a mind beyond limits. Together, they forge the Elliott-DARYL Combined Technology Initiator from junkyard scraps and a rare Alpha Crystal, racing against time to stop a global meltdown. No aliens, no bullshitвҖ”just human guts and raw ingenuity. <em>E.T.: Redux</em>вҖ”the future isnвҖҷt found; itвҖҷs built.вҖқ</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Plot Rundown:</strong> ElliottвҖҷs a scrappy kid scavenging the woods when he stumbles on D.A.R.Y.L., a pint-sized android who bolted from a shady lab. Dr. SmithвҖҷs teamвҖ”think grizzled engineers and rogue codersвҖ”has been chasing a breakthrough in quantum tech, but itвҖҷs spiraling toward a meltdown thatвҖҷll fry half the grid. Elliott and D.A.R.Y.L. team up, cobbling together the EDCTI from busted radios, car parts, and that elusive Alpha CrystalвҖ”a glowing relic from a defunct reactor. They crack the techвҖҷs code, reroute the overload, and save the day, proving brains and hustle trump miracles.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>EDCTI Details:</strong> This junkyard FrankensteinвҖҷs a beastвҖ”sensors from old TVs, gears from a wrecked Chevy, and D.A.R.Y.L.вҖҷs AI jacked into a busted laptop. The Alpha CrystalвҖҷs the kickerвҖ”rare as hell, scavenged from a Cold War ruin, it amplifies the rigвҖҷs signal to hack the quantum grid. ItвҖҷs duct-tape science with a PhD, and it works because these two misfits donвҖҷt know when to quit.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Even with its flaws, <em>E.T.</em>вҖ”alien or notвҖ”nails the human itch to push past the ordinary. This remake keeps that fire but ditches the fairy dust for sweat and steel, showing kids and adults alike that real wins come from grinding, not wishing.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Now, letвҖҷs veer off the rails. This whole child genius crap? ItвҖҷs the same horseshit that fuels those insufferable parents bragging about their вҖңgiftedвҖқ brats at PTA meetingsвҖ”meanwhile, little TimmyвҖҷs just good at Minecraft because heвҖҷs got no bedtime. And donвҖҷt get me started on the anti-adult vibeвҖ”SpielbergвҖҷs out here acting like grown-ups are the enemy, but last I checked, kids arenвҖҷt paying the bills or inventing penicillin. If <em>E.T.</em>вҖҷs right, we should all just ditch school, adopt a robot, and wait for the world to applaud our brilliance. Fuck thatвҖ”give me a whiskey and a wrench, and IвҖҷll outsmart any bike-flying punk any day. WhatвҖҷs your next move, you chaotic genius? LetвҖҷs keep this shitstorm rolling!</p></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @xl/mainview:top-0 @[960px]/mainview:block top-12 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mt-2 -ml-12 -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.5